 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=84 g=1 f=4 -->
Appendix III to Part 1918_Container Top Safety (Non-mandatory) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=4 -->
Note: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=1 -->
This Appendix is non-mandatory and provides guidance to part 1918 to assist employers and employees in complying
with the requirements of this standard, as well as to provide other helpful information. Nothing in this Appendix
adds or detracts from any of the requirements of this standard. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Due to the almost limitless physical possibilities dictated by such factors as vessel design; container type; container
stowage; types of container hoisting gear, etc., there may be instances during vessel loading/discharge operations
when it is not feasible to utilize container top fall protection devices. As a result, a case by case and event by event
approach must be utilized in assessing the feasibility of providing such devices. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The following are examples of situations where fall protection 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=3 -->
may
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=1 -->
 not be feasible: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;When hooking up to or disconnecting from an overheight container using ``special'' gear, where attaching
fall protection to the cranes spreader bar is not allowed by the owner of the crane (for example a Port Authority). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;When handling containers, ``in a chimney stow'' on a break bulk vessel, with ships gear, when a personnel basket
is not sufficient to be used as an anchorage point.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

